@page "/docs/animate-presence"

<PageTitle>AnimatePresence — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / <span>AnimatePresence</span></div>
<h1>AnimatePresence</h1>
<p>Wrap conditional content in <code>&lt;AnimatePresence&gt;</code> to animate elements as they enter <em>and</em> leave the DOM.</p>

<h2>Basic usage</h2>
<pre><code>&lt;AnimatePresence&gt;
    @@if (show)
    {
        &lt;Motion Tag="div"
                Initial="@@(new AnimationProps { Opacity = 0, Y = -20 })"
                Animate="@@(new AnimationProps  { Opacity = 1, Y = 0 })"
                Exit="@@(new AnimationProps     { Opacity = 0, Y = 20 })"
                Transition="@@(new TransitionConfig { Duration = 0.3 })"&gt;
            I animate in and out!
        &lt;/Motion&gt;
    }
&lt;/AnimatePresence&gt;

@@code {
    bool show = true;
}</code></pre>

<div class="demo-area" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;align-items:center;">
    <button class="demo-button" @onclick="Toggle">Toggle</button>
    <AnimatePresence>
        @if (_show)
        {
            <Motion Class="demo-box"
                    Initial="@(new AnimationProps { Opacity = 0, Scale = 0.5 })"
                    Animate="@(new AnimationProps { Opacity = 1, Scale = 1 })"
                    Exit="@(new AnimationProps   { Opacity = 0, Scale = 0.5 })"
                    Transition="@(new TransitionConfig { Type = TransitionType.Spring, Stiffness = 300, Damping = 20 })">
                Hello!
            </Motion>
        }
    </AnimatePresence>
</div>

<h2>Exit animations</h2>
<p>The <code>Exit</code> prop on a <code>&lt;Motion&gt;</code> child defines the target state when the element is removed. BlazorMotion delays DOM removal until the exit animation completes.</p>

<h2>Multiple children</h2>
<p>AnimatePresence handles multiple switching children. Use a unique <code>key</code> to help BlazorMotion track which element is entering/leaving:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;AnimatePresence&gt;
    &lt;Motion key="@@currentPage" ...&gt;@@currentPage&lt;/Motion&gt;
&lt;/AnimatePresence&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>Mode options</h2>
<table class="prop-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td>Mode</td><td>string</td><td>"sync" (default) — enter and exit simultaneously. "wait" — wait for exit to complete before entering.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> Always wrap route-level <code>@@Body</code> or conditional page content in <code>&lt;AnimatePresence&gt;</code> for smooth page transitions.
</div>

@code {
    bool _show = true;
    void Toggle() => _show = !_show;
}
